features: Take your gaming skills to the next level: The Logitech G413 SE is a full-size keyboard with gaming-first features and the durability and performance necessary to compete
PBT keycaps: Heat- and wear-resistant, this computer gaming keyboard features the most durable material used in keycap design
Tactile mechanical switches: Uncompromising performance is always within reach with this wired gaming keyboard
Premium color, material and finish: Elevate your gaming setup with this backlit keyboard featuring a sleek, black-brushed aluminum top case and white LED lighting
6-Key rollover anti-ghosting performance: Experience reliable key input with this anti-ghosting keyboard versus non-gaming mechanical keyboards
FN key media controls: Twelve (12) function (FN) keys let you control volume, play and pause, skip track, mute, toggle lighting, Windows lock, etc
Robust body design with minimal flex: The brushed aluminum-magnesium alloy top case serves as the corded keyboard’s backbone
Tenkeyless option: A compact, TKL layout is also available (Logitech G413 TKL SE)
body.description: Upgrade your gameplay experience with the Logitech G413 SE Full-Size Mechanical Gaming Keyboard. It delivers a gaming-grade mechanical switch experience. It’s designed to help serious players perform at a higher level and push themselves even further. The G413 SE features tactile mechanical switches; PBT keycaps, 6-key rollover anti-ghosting performance; a black-brushed aluminum top case with white LED lighting; 12 function key media controls; and reliable USB-corded technology. A compact, tenkeyless option is available. In short, the gaming-first features you need to put more perfect performance within reach. A keyboard engineered to perform. A keyboard that’s Made for Play.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Price, Great feel, Great look and Great Sound
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. If you are looking for a great mechanical keyboard and don’t want to deal with all the BS that doesn’t matter, this is the keyboard to buy. Especially if you can find on sale as I did and get for $50 or under.I needed a new keyboard to complete my home nerd center where I work and play video games. I went from the Dell Membrane keyboard that my employer gave me to this MechanicalKeyboard after going through three keyboards due to how much I use, I also type hard. This checked all the boxes for me and I love it so very much.Great look with its brushed aluminum top plate to keep these wonderful feeling PBT keys and brown switches in place. There isn’t software to run RGB and you have 5-6 different lighting settings that’s controlled with Function F12, perfection. I didn’t want another program to run on my PC and the default lights are bright, clear and look clean with the white. In the middle of the day the keys are easy to read and see, when keyboard lights are out the keys look black. Lights reset after every power down cycle on your computer so if that’s something that annoys you maybe buy something else, for me this is exactly what I needed.The feel and sound of the keys and switches are great. I type hard and the longer throw of the keys and feel of them is just wonderful. The sound makes me happy and the feel has me wanting to type up rants to all my exes.In love! Great price and Great feel. Video included so y’all’s can hear the wonderful sounds emanating from this great product.Update; still in love swooning out here. Including pics of some keycaps that look sexy. Pics do no justice how good these white keys made it. Duel colorway is the best.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very nice keyboard!
reviews.reviewText: I'm not a gamer and just wanted a very good quality, backlit keyboard. I don't like these newer keyboards that have basically flat keys; I prefer the good, tactile feel of the keys on this one and like having the full travel and responsive feedback of the keys on this Logitech keyboard.The backlighting is very nice and the key fonts are bold, bright, and easy to read. It's simple and just white color, which I also like, as I don't care about having different colors and effects.I got this one to replace another, similar gaming keyboard, of which two had gone bad, with LEDs going out and eventually keys not working. Hoping this name-brand one will last longer. I'm not a hard user, so I feel that something like this should last longer than the others did.The keys on this one are not as 'clicky' as the old one was, but they are still perfect for me, as they feel just as responsive, but aren't quite as noisy.So far I give this a full five stars, because it works exceptionally well and feels solid and well-made. I would definitely recommend it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent keyboard! One drawback.....
reviews.reviewText: Great build, love the feel. I was actually hoping for a little louder of the clicky sound. But it does have a good sound to it. Probably would be annoying in an open cubicle office environment like others say. The ONLY drawback for me is I wish the function keys lit up where the icons are for what the function keys do. If your keyboard area isn't well lit you can't see those icons AT ALL. I considered taking a star off for this issue but I like the keyboard enough to not take off one star. It is just the right size for me. Straight and simple design and the backlighting is great! Highly recommend for someone looking for a straight simple keyboard that gets the job done.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 29, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This is not going to give you that a CherryMX mechanical keyboard sound and feel. It's nice to type on, responsive, and works on my Mac and PC, but it still feels like you're typing on a high-end plastic keyboard, and not a true mechanical one. Also the lighting doesn't stay on the same setting after a reboot; kind of annoying.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 26, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This Logitech is fantastic, with its keys being less noisy and very satisfying to the impact this is a wonderful choice! If you want a mechanical but don’t want the green or blue switches. This is a nice more quiet variety. It’ll still click, but it isn’t a clack fest. Enough about sound and impact. Function keys work well and is compatible with the steam deck! Solid choice in response and ergonomics and will last due to proper quality as Logitech is known for. If you want a clean setup for the office with better feel than a basic keyboard this is great. If you are a gamer you will love it! This is a well rounded and tasteful mechanical keyboard!It’s worth it’s value and price, also the white backlights are great in low light situations!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars good keyboard for typing
reviews.reviewText: nothing crazy the white lights are bright, the keys are abit more farapart then i liked and have high key channels making it abit harder to my from one key to the next fast, and not all keys are back light, they do give u some options on the keyboard it self for fancey light use but no RGB and no support for Logitech hub,i returned it for the g513,and im kinda want this one back lol

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I wanted a good but cheaper backlit keyboard for work. This fits the bill perfectly.It is not software controlled so I don’t have to install stuff in the work computer. It has mechanical keys. It is definitely louder than membrane but not enough to disturb people around me. I do a lot of work in the dark so the backlight is a godsend for me. The construction quality is great.I like this keyboard a lot and would recommend it.

As a former office worker I give this top grades for being a dream to type on. Takes a little getting used to but vastly superior to a normal keyboard. I doubt I’ll have to replace it as it is sturdy as heck. It does light up of its own accord and it does make enough sound for everyone to know you are working. I like that it is wired as there is no delay when you start typing. Highly recommended.

reviews.reviewTitle: buena calida por lo que pagas
reviews.reviewText: Muy buen teclado si solo quieres escribir y jugar y si no te importan las luces
Misma tipologia y respuesta de cualquier teclado de logitech, una sensacion genial al usarlo por varias horas, simplemente excelso.
Works perfect led effects amazing and it’s huge too

Me llegó el mismo día que lo pedí, todo se siente de muy buena calidad, se siente robusto y de buen material, las luces Led tienen buen brillo en mi opinión y tienen la opción de cambiar la intensidad, lo único que me hubiera gustado es el puerto usb que tiene el g413 normal pero de ahí en fuera estoy contento con el teclado.
